l_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"http://www.totalbounty.com/?p=1044";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:152:"<p>Total Bounty&#8482; is proud to announce that our latest seller &#8220;Ten Ton Books&#8221; has released a video tutorial course to teach you ...</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Total Bounty";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7091:"<p>Total Bounty&trade; is proud to announce that our latest seller &#8220;Ten Ton Books&#8221; has released a video tutorial course to teach you &#8220;<a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/mkt/item/scratch-building-wordpress-themes-with-photoshop">How to Create a WordPress Theme</a> from scratch in Photoshop!</p>\n<p>This unique and easy to follow WordPress theme video tutorial includes more than 13 hours of content, and supporting course materials are included.  You will learn everything from how to create a theme template design using a grid based template system, to how to move that design into HTML, CSS, and PHP code to create your very own custom WordPress theme.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/mkt/item/scratch-building-wordpress-themes-with-photoshop"><img src="http://www.totalbounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/create-custom-wordpress-theme-300x168.jpg" alt="How to Create a Custom WordPress Theme" title="create-custom-wordpress-theme" width="300" height="168" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1045" /></a></p>\n<p>Each chapter has multiple lessons, here are the 11 chapter titles:</p>\n<p>Chapter 1: Introduction<br />\nChapter 2: Setting Up Photoshop for Web Layout!<br />\nChapter 3: Getting Set Up for User Interface Design!<br />\nChapter 4: Developing A Wireframe UI in Photoshop!<br />\nChapter 5: Finishing Up the Wireframe!<br />\nChapter 6: From Wireframe to Design!<br />\nChapter 7: Applying Photography and Textures!<br />\nChapter 8: Preparing A Blank WordPress Theme for Design!<br />\nChapter 9: Building The WordPress Theme From Complete Scratch!<br />\nChapter 10: Pushing the Theme Design Further!<br />\nChapter 11: Wrapping Things Up!</p>\n<p>This WordPress theme course is for intermediate to advanced levels, and have at least a basic understanding of HTML, CSS, and Photoshop (know your way around and be at least a tiny bit dangerous).</p>\n<p>Still not convinced that you will easily learn how to code and slice a WordPress theme from PSD?  Here are four full lesson videos ripped directly from the WordPress theme course:</p>\n<p><b>Building a Custom Grid System (13 minutes)</b></p>\n<p>This 13 minute video from Chapter 3, Lesson 3 is a small sample of what you&#8217;ll learn in this 13 hour course.  Many designers use web grid systems for faster standardized layout when creating WordPress themes.  It&#8217;s a great way to wireframe a design.</p>\n<p><iframe id="viddler-7a8e9821" src="//www.viddler.com/embed/7a8e9821/?f=1&#038;offset=0&#038;autoplay=0&#038;secret=51471048&#038;disablebranding=0&#038;view_secret=51471048" width="545" height="349" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\n<p><b>Saving Out Custom Photoshop Color Palettes (3 minutes)</b></p>\n<p>This video shows how to save a palatte of colors in Photoshop to use throughout your design (to load all at once later).  It keeps things organized throughout the design process.</p>\n<p><iframe id="viddler-c78ab557" src="//www.viddler.com/embed/c78ab557/?f=1&#038;offset=0&#038;autoplay=0&#038;secret=31062984&#038;disablebranding=0" width="545" height="349" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\n<p><b>Extracting Content from Photoshop and Inserting It Into a WordPress Theme (9 minutes)</b></p>\n<p>This video shows you how to pull a web design from a PSD template file you&#8217;ve created and extract and slice those graphics for insertion into an installable WordPress theme file via CSS.</p>\n<p><iframe id="viddler-e32e2e5b" src="//www.viddler.com/embed/e32e2e5b/?f=1&#038;offset=0&#038;autoplay=0&#038;secret=106592368&#038;disablebranding=0" width="545" height="349" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\n<p><b>Custom WordPress Category and Search Pages (8 minutes)</b></p>\n<p>In this video you learn about how things translate from a PSD Photoshop design to CSS and HTML code in a WordPress theme &#8211; like single post pages, commenting areas, and even archive pages like category and search results.</p>\n<p><iframe id="viddler-9ee45c8" src="//www.viddler.com/embed/9ee45c8/?f=1&#038;offset=0&#038;autoplay=0&#038;secret=100595426&#038;disablebranding=0" width="545" height="349" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\n<p>So, now that you&#8217;ve seen actual course material and how easy it is to follow &#8211; are you ready to start building your first WordPress theme?</p>\n<p>Normally paying a WordPress developer or company to build a WordPress theme from a PSD design from scratch could cost any where from $800-$1,500 per theme (for quality work).</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a designer who has yet to code their first theme &#8211; look at the money you could be making, you&#8217;re leaving money on the table each and every day you don&#8217;t have this skill!</p>\n<p>If you just want to code your own WordPress theme for the first time for your own website, this course easily costs more than 10X less that what it would cost to pay someone to code that theme (and you&#8217;ll have the skills to code as many themes as you want in the future on your own).</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?  Learn how to <a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/mkt/item/scratch-building-wordpress-themes-with-photoshop">Create a Custom WordPress Theme</a> on your own today!</p>\n<div class="aizattos_related_posts"><span class="aizattos_related_posts_header" >Related Posts</span><ul><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/1002/how-to-theme-your-wordpress-login-page/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: How to Theme Your WordPress Login Page" >How to Theme Your WordPress Login Page</a></span><div class="aizattos_related_posts_excerpt">Have you ever wanted to modify or "theme" your WordPress login page?  Maybe for yourself, or maybe f...</div></li><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/499/how-to-create-pdfs-in-wordpress/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: How to Create PDFs in WordPress" >How to Create PDFs in WordPress</a></span><div class="aizattos_related_posts_excerpt">Sometimes you might have a WordPress website where you want to offer the end user the option to down...</div></li><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/165/modify-your-theme-for-excerpts-of-posts/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: Modify Your Theme for Excerpts of Posts" >Modify Your Theme for Excerpts of Posts</a></span><div class="aizattos_related_posts_excerpt">Have you ever wondered why some WordPress powered websites have excerpts of posts on certain pages, ...</div></li><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/1011/build-a-wordpress-website-video-tutorial/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: Build a WordPress Website Video Tutorial" >Build a WordPress Website Video Tutorial</a></span></li><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/316/how-to-exclude-pages-from-navigation-menus-in-wordpress/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: How to Exclude Pages from Navigation Menus in WordPress" >How to Exclude Pages from Navigation Menus in WordPress</a></span></li></ul></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0