eleased a new video tutorial course in the marketplace &#8220;<a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/mkt/item/how-to-build-a-wordpress-website-in-a-day">How to Build a WordPress Website in a Day</a>. If you&#8217;ve ever wanted to learn how to build your own website on the WordPress platform &#8211; with your own domain name and webhosting account, this 5 hour, 16 video module tutorial class is exactly what you&#8217;ve been looking for!</p>\n<p>The greatest thing about WordPress is that it&#8217;s free open source software to manage your website. It doesn&#8217;t cost any money, and any one can use it. There are thousands of blog posts and free tutorials online describing how to make it do just about anything you want within a website. There are dozens of books for sale as well. The problem is, there is really no good &#8220;start here&#8221; guide if you&#8217;ve never purchased a domain name, don&#8217;t know what &#8220;webhosting&#8221; is, and have never seen WordPress before. Just because 70+ million people use it to manage their websites, doesn&#8217;t mean that the rest of the planet is even aware of what it is just yet.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/mkt/item/how-to-build-a-wordpress-website-in-a-day"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-1012" title="how-to-build-wordpress-website" src="http://www.totalbounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/how-to-build-wordpress-website.jpg" alt="How to Build a WordPress website" width="600" height="407" /></a></p>\n<p>The author of this course, <a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/public_profile/seller/231">Mark Copeman</a>, from Berks, United Kingdom &#8211; is not a web designer, programmer, or developer. If you&#8217;re not a technical person, this is probably great news to you &#8211; because a great majority of content online for WordPress is created by tech people, leaving you on your own to figure out the learning curve.</p>\n<p>This WordPress video tutorial series doesn&#8217;t focus on the computer screen all the time (like many do), refreshingly he writes a lot of the ideas out on paper right before your very eyes, while explaining all the thoughts and concepts clearly and directly &#8211; in a language that everyone can easily understand.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example from the &#8220;How to Choose a Domain Name&#8221; video module:</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1013" title="how-to-choose-a-domain-name" src="http://www.totalbounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/how-to-choose-a-domain-name.jpg" alt="How to Choose a Domain Name" width="509" height="276" /></p>\n<p>Many of the video modules take you from computer screen to paper and back, here&#8217;s an example of a screencast in progress for &#8220;How to Install and Configure a WordPress Theme&#8221;:</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1014" title="installing-configuring-wordpress-theme" src="http://www.totalbounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/installing-configuring-wordpress-theme.jpg" alt="How to install and configure a WordPress theme" width="465" height="243" /></p>\n<p>With this course you get 16 separate videos walking you through the process of creating a WordPress powered website in 1 day, including buying your domain name, setting up webhosting and email, installing and configuring WordPress, and setting up themes and plugins.</p>\n<p>Here are all 16 video modules:</p>\n<p>Module 1: How to choose a domain name<br />\nDuration: 24 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 2: How to choose a web hosting provider<br />\nDuration: 26 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 3: Buying your domain and getting started with your server<br />\nDuration: 20 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 4: Introduction to WordPress<br />\nDuration: 19 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 5: How to install WordPress<br />\nDuration: 23 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 6: Getting your site right first on paper<br />\nDuration: 22 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 7: First steps with WordPress<br />\nDuration: 15 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 8: How to select a theme/design for your site<br />\nDuration: 19 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 9: Installing and configuring your theme<br />\nDuration: 21 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 10: Setting up your navigation<br />\nDuration: 15 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 11: Sidebars and Widgets<br />\nDuration: 21 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 12: Creating your first pages<br />\nDuration: 25 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 13: Setting up your blog and making a post<br />\nDuration: 17 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 14: Installing the essential plugins<br />\nDuration: 13 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 15: Setting up your email<br />\nDuration: 11 minutes</p>\n<p>Module 16: A tour of the finished site<br />\nDuration: 20 minutes</p>\n<p>To purchase this video course, visit the <a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/shop/mkt/item/how-to-build-a-wordpress-website-in-a-day">How to Build a WordPress Website in 1 Day</a> item page in the Total Bounty™ marketplace.</p>\n<div class="aizattos_related_posts"><span class="aizattos_related_posts_header" >Related Posts</span><ul><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/1149/wordpress-qr-code-tutorial-video/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress QR Code Tutorial Video" >WordPress QR Code Tutorial Video</a></span><div class="aizattos_related_posts_excerpt">Even if you don''t own a website, odds are you''ve heard of a QR code.  You may think these little sca...</div></li><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/376/wordpress-text-message-video-tutorial/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress Text Message Video Tutorial" >WordPress Text Message Video Tutorial</a></span><div class="aizattos_related_posts_excerpt">\r\n\r\nEarlier this week we announced that WordPress Text Message v. 2.03 was released, and Total Bount...</div></li><li><span class="aizattos_related_posts_title"><a href="http://www.totalbounty.com/299/how-to-setup-jetpack-plugin-in-wordpress-part-2/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: How to Setup Jet